message.content:
A bee is an insect that belongs to the Hymenoptera order.
They typically have black and yellow striped bodies, with fuzzy texture and slender shape.
The wings of a bee are typically translucent and veined.
On their heads, bees have two compound eyes and three simple eyes.
They are known for their ability to collect nectar and pollen from flowers, which they store in hives.
Bees are commonly found in gardens, meadows, and other natural habitats.
They play a vital role in pollinating plants, making them essential to ecosystems and agriculture.
